---
title: Introducing the GetHired MCP Server
image: /images/posts/introducing-the-get-hired-mcp-server/image.jpg
---
We’re excited to launch the GetHired MCP Server — a new way to connect AI tools like Cursor and Claude directly to your GetHired account.

This means your AI assistant can now securely access your jobs, resumes, applications, and profile information through the Model Context Protocol (MCP).

## What Does This Enable?

With the GetHired MCP Server, compatible AI clients can:

- Search for jobs from GetHired
- Retrieve relevant jobs based on your profile
- Access saved and applied jobs
- Fetch resume details and resume reviews
- Use your GetHired data directly inside AI workflows

Instead of manually copying information between platforms, your AI tools can now work with your GetHired data in real time.

## Supported Clients

The MCP server has been tested with:

- Cursor
- Claude Desktop
- MCP Inspector

We’re continuing to improve compatibility across additional MCP clients.

## Secure Authentication

The GetHired MCP Server uses OAuth 2.1 for HTTP-based clients.

When connecting through clients like Cursor:

1. You’ll be redirected to GetHired
1. You approve access
1. The AI client is securely connected to your account

No manual token pasting is required for supported HTTP clients.

For local stdio clients like Claude Desktop, users can generate an API token from their GetHired dashboard.

## Why We Built This

AI-native workflows are quickly becoming the default way developers and professionals interact with software.

We wanted GetHired to be accessible not only through the web app, but also through AI agents, coding assistants, and automation tools.

The MCP Server is the first step toward making GetHired programmable and AI-native.

